        <h1>PRIVACY POLICY</h1>
             <p>
                 At ABAP, we are committed to protecting your privacy and earning your trust. We want to let you know what kind of personal information we have about you, and how we use and share it. It also describes the choices available to you regarding our use of your personal information and how you can access and update this information.
                 If you have an unresolved privacy or data use concern that we have not addressed satisfactorily
             </p>
        <h2>What Information Do We Collect and How Do We Get It?</h2>
             <p>
                 ABAP collects a variety of information that will aid us in quoting and servicing your insurance policy and providing the Service to you. This information includes "non public personal information", which is all information that identifies you and is not available to the public.
                 Here are some examples of the information we get:
             </P>
             <h4>Application and Communications:</h4>
                 
             <P>Through the App and the Service we gather  information such as your name, address, residential information, phone number, driver’s license number,  social security number, gender, date of birth, educational background, occupational information, former  insurance information, vehicle information, marital status and driving history, as well as other information  that you may provide through other communication features of the Service.
              </P>
              <h4>Consumer Report:</h4> 
             <P>Through consumer reporting agencies we gather information such as your driving record, claims history with other insurers, credit report and insurance score. These agencies keep your information and only disclose it to us as permitted by law. By submitting an application for coverage, you authorize ABAP to request your credit report.
             </P>
         <h4>Transactions:</h4> 
                <P>Through your transactions with us, we gather information such as insurance coverage, payments and claims history, and payment instrument information, such as credit card information.
                </P>
         <h4>Website Usage:</h4>
              <P> Like most online services, when you use the Service, we may automatically collect certain information about your visit and store it in log files, such as the website and/or search criteria that led you to our Service, your Internet Protocol address (“IP Address”), UDID, or other device address or ID, device type, operating system, browser info, and what pages you visit on the Service, the web pages or sites that you visit just before or just after the Service.
              </P>
        
         <h2>The Ways ABAP Uses Information</h2>
             <P>ABAP uses the information you provide or that we collect to develop, operate, maintain, enhance, and provide all of the features and services found on the Service now and in the future, and to service your account with us, including the following:
              We may use "automatically collected" information and "cookies" information to:<br/> 
              (a) personalize our services, such as remembering your information so that you will not have to re-enter it during your visit or the next time you use the Service;<br/>
              (b) provide customized third party advertisements, content, and information<br/>
              (c) monitor and analyze the effectiveness of the Service and third party marketing activities
             </p>
         <h2>Communications with ABAP</h2>
             <p>As a policyholder, we will contact you regarding your policy, such as billing notices and confirmations of changes, through email. We will also use your email to provide you with updates about our products and services. We may also contact you by phone regarding timely matters such as late payment or other factors that might affect your policy.
             </p>
         <h2>Import Contacts</h2>
             <p>You can import contacts from your Gmail or other email account address book to invite them to become members of our website. We collect the username and password for the email account from which you wish to import your contacts, and will only use your personal information for that purpose.
             </p>
           <h2>Contact Information</h2>
             <p>For any questions about our privacy policy, please contact us using this online form.

              Call Customer Service at 888-244-1702.
